  "title": "Assistant Vice President – Information Technology Department",
  "description": "<h3><em>Job Duties:</em></h3><ul><li>Promote IT initiatives across Asia for both life and P & C, spanning 8 countries and 13 entities.</li><li>Promote the IT strategy of the Asian region and to align it with the global IT strategy and to formulate and lead projects that can contribute to the Asia region.</li><li>In addition to strategy construction, also create concrete IT plans and lead and support local implementation.</li><li>Lead the regional implementation of regional programs, providing promising value to customers and partners in all Asian countries.</li><li> Overseas’ business travels are required.</li></ul><h3><em>Requirements:</em></h3><ul><li>University Degree with professional IT qualifications.</li><li>At least 10 years' experience in an insurance company and over 5 years' experience in IT lead.</li><li>Leadership roles across Local and Regional Geographies.</li><li>Complex Project Management; Implementation of cutting-edge IT solutions.</li><li>Extensive experience in IT partnerships, sales & marketing, etc.</li><li>Management of large delivery teams working with cross functional units and third-party vendors.</li><li>Proficiency in Japanese language is required to liaise with Japan HQ and to read Japanese reports/documents.</li><li>Good written report, presentation and communication skills in both English and Japanese language.</li></ul>",
